# Cursor Rules — Maverick Business Academy (mbaLondon)

## Read these first, in order, before any task
1. PROJECT_CONTEXT.md — current state of the codebase
2. docs/08-AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md — full AI working rules (file-reading
   strategy, critical rules, output rules, workflows)

Then read only what's relevant to the specific task, per the table in
docs/08-AI_INSTRUCTIONS.md.

## Absolute rules
- Do NOT modify any existing `.html`, `.css`, or `.js` file in this repo
  unless the task explicitly requires it, and never touch `/assets`
  unless explicitly asked.
- Tech stack for Phase 1 is **Next.js + Payload CMS 3.x (installed
  natively inside the Next.js app) + MySQL + Cloudinary + Cloudflare +
  Zoho + Zapier**. The previously-planned PHP/custom-admin-panel
  approach is scrapped — never reference or build it.
- Homepage conversion to Next.js must be pixel-identical: 0% visual or
  feature change from the current prototype.
- Inner pages reuse the homepage's design system but use less
  animation, for load performance.
- Every page (static Global or dynamic Collection entry) requires the
  mandatory SEO field group: title, description, keywords, slug, schema
  JSON, scripts. No exceptions.
- Program detail pages require an unlimited FAQ repeater field.
- Don't invent new Payload fields/collections without checking
  docs/12-PAYLOAD_SCHEMA.md first.

